<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="ddu7v1" data-video-descrip="Realizing love conquers all, Elsa finally learns to control her powers and ends the endless winter for good." data-video-title="The Great Thaw" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/ddu7v1_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/ddu7v1.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ThePowerOfLove" data-video-tropename="The Power of Love" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/Frozen2013" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/ddu7v1.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">The Great Thaw</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="tu9qrh" data-video-descrip="In the infamous betrayal scene from Frozen, Prince Hans states that he faked his romance with Anna just so he can seize the throne of Arendelle and overthrow Elsa when the right moment strikes. With Anna dying from the icy heart curse accidentally placed by Elsa, he even gloats about it in her face, leaving her despondent." data-video-title="Prince Hans Treachery" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/tu9qrh_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/screen_shot_2020_06_08_at_102913_am.png" data-video-trope="Main/FauxAffablyEvil" data-video-tropename="Faux Affably Evil" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/Frozen2013" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/screen_shot_2020_06_08_at_102913_am.png">
<p><span class="bold">Prince Hans Tre...</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="py75it" data-video-descrip="When Elsa finds out Anna got engaged to Hans within just one day of meeting, she delivers real-life advice." data-video-title="Frozen" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/py75it_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/py75it.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/TruthInTelevision" data-video-tropename="Truth in Television" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/Frozen2013" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/py75it.jpg">
